      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can't provide medical advice; however, I can offer some general information about blood thinners. When tapering warfarin, it's generally recommended to gradually decrease the dose under medical supervision to minimize the risk of clotting or bleeding complications. Generally, a dose reduction is typically no more than 25-50% every 4-6 weeks, with regular INR monitoring to ensure the target range is maintained.",
